2500|$|Kantianism is a {{philosophy}} {{based on the}} ethical, epistemological, and metaphysical works of Immanuel Kant. Kant {{is known for his}} deontological theory where there is <b>a</b> single <b>moral</b> <b>obligation,</b> the [...] "Categorical Imperative", derived from the concept of duty. Kantians believe all actions are performed in accordance with some underlying maxim or principle, and for actions to be ethical, they must adhere to the categorical imperative.|$|R
